{
  "stem": "8784.5",
  "chunk_idx": 8,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 8.6,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 70,
      "text": "And this was the fellow, Adam Mandel that arrived from the transport of-- so this was the closest person that I found that I could somebody I know close, outside of my family, because no one in my family was left alive.",
      "word_count": 42
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 71,
      "text": "From the liquidation on, of the ghetto, I never found anyone alive.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 72,
      "text": "And later on, we developed a-- a sort of a friendship with Adam, where we continued together.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 73,
      "text": "We-- shortly thereafter, we left from Poland and went to Czechoslovakia, thinking that in Czechoslovakia we will escape communism, because we didn't really know the political situation that well.",
      "word_count": 29
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 74,
      "text": "We were youngsters.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 75,
      "text": "But we discovered quickly that-- and we did like the Czechoslovak people.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 76,
      "text": "The Czechoslovak people are extremely friendly people.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 77,
      "text": "And we thought Czechoslovakia was the place to settle.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 78,
      "text": "And we did settle for awhile, until maybe the end of summer of 1945.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 79,
      "text": "At the end of summer, we recognized that the-- that the Czechoslovakia is equally occupied by the Russians, and this is also not a safe place to-- to stay.",
      "word_count": 29
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 80,
      "text": "And we-- again, there was no-- no functioning organizations to take you any place yet.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 81,
      "text": "This was too early, a little too early.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 82,
      "text": "And so we had to be geniuses, just like Schindler had to be a genius, to cross the borders.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 83,
      "text": "Now, all of the sudden I found myself in that same situation, that I had to be a genius to cross illegally borders.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 84,
      "text": "I had to cross from Poland into Czechoslovakia illegally.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 85,
      "text": "In fact, I went with a Russian soldier.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 86,
      "text": "I discovered that there is some place a Russian soldier that, for a bottle of vodka, he'll take you on a-- on a big truck that he holds potatoes on.",
      "word_count": 30
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 87,
      "text": "He's got the potatoes covered with straw.",
      "word_count": 7
    }
  ],
